cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a novel approach for template matching that relies on both local appearance and geometric information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed method is robust to complex deformations, significant background clutter, and occlusions, which indicates that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The empirical evaluation on a benchmark dataset suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as these fields often involve the use of benchmark datasets for evaluation.
